Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[TextData[StyleBox["The quantum phase", "Subsection"]], "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.927981097803137*^9, 3.927981102697281*^9}},
 CellID->1943136,ExpressionUUID->"f47710f4-4ade-374d-aed5-77d56a3e10c6"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "There have been many attempts to define a quantum phase. Dirac proposed a \
polar decomposition and assumed a Hermitian phase operator. However, it can \
be shown that exp(\[ImaginaryI] ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    OverscriptBox["\[Phi]", "^"], ")"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "48844ad4-aaf8-8949-bc5e-05a2643cdb7a"],
 " cannot be unitary; hence ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    OverscriptBox["\[Phi]", "^"], " ", "cannot", " ", "be"}], 
   TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->"cdf4d910-661b-324b-ba46-484b5097ea6c"],
 " Hermitian. Barnett and Pegg proposed unitary operators of the form ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["e", 
    RowBox[{" ", 
     RowBox[{"\[ImaginaryI]", " ", 
      OverscriptBox["\[Phi]", "^"]}]}]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "83f69964-f2d0-bf4a-8294-5f5ff5d0fa21"],
 ", but that construction introduces unphysical negative-number states and \
does not add new physical predictions. Additional difficulties arise because ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   OverscriptBox["\[Phi]", "^"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "adf4f195-943a-e048-9a53-cbd36e43f4a8"],
 " must be an angle operator, which leads to problematic relations when \
angular momentum is considered."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9314511799911175`*^9, 3.9314511835074654`*^9}, {
   3.9314512327733803`*^9, 3.931451267237255*^9}, {3.9314513083656254`*^9, 
   3.9314513148068676`*^9}, {3.9314513528377495`*^9, 3.931451375911337*^9}, {
   3.9314518776625557`*^9, 3.931451883843151*^9}, {3.9314519200494957`*^9, 
   3.9314519625804386`*^9}, {3.9314542816604023`*^9, 
   3.9314542827340584`*^9}, {3.9314554849932346`*^9, 3.931455573450943*^9}, {
   3.931455605122711*^9, 3.931455649410427*^9}, {3.9314558624459743`*^9, 
   3.931455894288477*^9}, {3.9314559874109497`*^9, 3.9314560403012657`*^9}, 
   3.9314561003934536`*^9, {3.9314561321518383`*^9, 3.9314561636282387`*^9}, {
   3.965210228401888*^9, 3.965210322375759*^9}, {3.965210355598768*^9, 
   3.9652104003576965`*^9}},
 CellID->394509151,ExpressionUUID->"8106e973-7b7b-a444-a61e-1299d1b8e09a"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "We follow the formalism introduced by Susskind and Glogower. The \
Susskind-Glogower operator ",
 StyleBox["Susskind",
  IgnoreSpellCheck->True],
 " is defined by:"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.93144843180355*^9, 3.931448476886603*^9}, {
  3.931448814202746*^9, 3.931448822013943*^9}, {3.931451505848089*^9, 
